@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - opa/OpaInstance
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired OpaInstance spec, tracked status,\nand delete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via\nGetOpaInstance;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListOpaInstances using filters compartmentId,\ndisplayName;
:Create the OCI resource via CreateOpaInstance\nwhen no reusable match is found;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path uses DeleteOpaInstance with\nrequired via GetOpaInstance or\nListOpaInstances to DELETED, NOT_FOUND\nconfirmation;
:Confirm deletion via GetOpaInstance or\nListOpaInstances until OCI reaches DELETED,\nNOT_FOUND;
if ("Delete cleanup and finalizer release succeed?") then (yes)
:Remove the finalizer after delete completion;
else (no)
:Stay blocked until cleanup or finalizer\nrelease succeeds;
endif
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state in retryable set?") then (yes)
:Request requeue while OCI remains in CREATING,\nUPDATING, DELETING;
stop
endif
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE, INACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the\nrepo-authored mutation surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields compartmentId, consumptionModel,\nidcsAt, isBreakglassEnabled (+2 more);
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply UpdateOpaInstance only for mutable\nfields definedTags, description, displayName,\nfreeformTags;
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=opainstance action=CREATED;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=opainstance action=UPDATED;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=opainstance action=DELETED when the\nmatching field-driven path executes;
:Apply explicit follow-up semantics\ncreate=GetWorkRequest -> GetOpaInstance;\nupdate=GetWorkRequest -> GetOpaInstance;\ndelete=GetWorkRequest ->\nGetOpaInstance/ListOpaInstances confirm-delete;
:Return success for the ACTIVE, INACTIVE\nsuccess state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nretain-until-confirmed-delete;
:Requeue on provisioning, updating, terminating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: opa
slug: opainstance
kind: OpaInstance
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update
UPDATING; delete DELETING
follow-up: create=GetWorkRequest ->
GetOpaInstance; update=GetWorkRequest ->
GetOpaInstance; delete=GetWorkRequest ->
GetOpaInstance/ListOpaInstances confirm-delete
supported drift: definedTags, description,
displayName, freeformTags
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartmentId, consumptionModel, idcsAt,
isBreakglassEnabled (+2 more)
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_opa_opa_instances filters
compartmentId, displayName; exact compartmentId
plus displayName unique match in ACTIVE,
CREATING, UPDATING, or INACTIVE; duplicate
matches fail
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE and
INACTIVE as success, and DELETING as
terminating; FAILED is terminal and DELETED is
only a delete-confirmation target.
Create, update, and delete responses expose
work-request headers but do not return an
OpaInstance body. The runtime resumes through
GetWorkRequest, recovers the affected
OpaInstance OCID from work-request resources,
and rereads GetOpaInstance before settling.
Pre-create reuse only runs when both
spec.compartmentId and spec.displayName are
present and keeps exact compartmentId plus
displayName matching bounded to ACTIVE,
CREATING, UPDATING, or INACTIVE summaries.
Only displayName, description, freeformTags, and
definedTags reconcile in place; IdcsAt is
create-time-only and normalized out of
post-create parity because OCI does not echo it,
while compartmentId, shapeName,
consumptionModel, meteringType, and
isBreakglassEnabled remain replacement-only.
ChangeOpaInstanceCompartment, StartOpaInstance,
and StopOpaInstance remain out of scope for the
published runtime surface. Delete keeps the
finalizer until the work request is terminal and
GetOpaInstance or fallback ListOpaInstances
confirms the resource is gone.
end note
@enduml
